help.ban: Ban members permanently from the server. The time to specify corresponds to the messages that will be deleted over time.
help.config: This is a command to configure the bot's settings for the server.²Define the role that a user will have when he arrives on a server.²Set the bot language for the server.²Change the bot prefix for the server.²Define the room where the announcements of the people who join or leave the server with his ID.²Add or removes a word from the list of forbidden words. Can even reset the entire list of forbidden words.

help.github: List all GitHub repositories or give information about a GitHub repository of a GitHub user/organization.
help.guildInfo: Give the nitro level, the owner of the server, the number of people not connected and connected on the server.
help.invite: Create a server invitation or give the bot's invitation link.
help.issue: Send an issue to our Github repository.
help.kick: Kick a server member, the person can join afterwards.
help.maths: This is a command with many uses related to mathematics.²Calculate the specified mathematical expression.²Calculate the specified mathematical expression.²Check if a number is prime or make a list of all prime numbers up to the specified number.²Check if a number is perfect or make a list of all perfect numbers up to the specified number.²Convert one unit of measurement to another.

help.purge: Delete messages that are less than 2 weeks old by a given number between 0 and 101.
help.say: Send the specified message and includes your name if you do not have permissions to manage messages.
help.snippet: Transform the specified code into an image.
help.spigot: Give the name, link, ID and description of a Spigot plugin by searching for it by its ID or by its name or search for a Spigot user.

help.translate: Translate the specified sentence according to the language of the text and the language you want the text to be translated from.

help.unmute: Unmute a member only if the user is already muted.

syntax.ban:
The time limit to be specified is 7 days.
If the specified time exceeds 7 days, it will be reset to 7 days.
The messages will be deleted according to the specified time.
Putting a reason is not mandatory.
syntax.channelMember:
The available arguments are:
- **join** will define the channel where the welcome announcements will appear.
- **leave** will define the channel where the departure announcements will appear.

After these arguments, the available arguments are **channel ID/mention**, **reset** and **this** :
- **channel ID/mention** will define the channel by its ID or mention.
- **reset** will reset the channel that has been configured.
- **this** will define the channel where the order was made.
syntax.createChannel:
The only two arguments to specify for the type are "**text**" and "**voice**"..
- The argument "**text**" will define a textual channel.
- The argument "**voice**" will define a voice room.
The name of the new salon must not exceed 100 characters.
You can choose to specify a category for the salon to be classified in or not.
syntax.invite:
The only two arguments available are **create** and **bot**.
The **create** argument will create a new server invitation link.
The **bot** argument will send the bot invitation link.
syntax.joinRole:
The available arguments are:
- **channel ID/mention** will define the role thanks to its ID or its mention.
- **reset** will reset the role that has been configured.
syntax.localization:
The available languages are:
:flag_us: / :flag_gb: en
:flag_fr: fr
If the language is not configured, it will default to English.
syntax.mute: Putting a reason is not mandatory.
syntax.prohibit:
The available arguments are **add**, **rem** and **reset**.
- **add** will add a word to the list of forbidden words.
- **rem** will remove a word from the list of prohibited words.
- **reset** will reset the entire list of forbidden words.
After the arguments **add** and **rem**, you must put the argument **word** which will correspond to the word that will be added or removed.
syntax.purge: The number of messages to specify must be between **0** and **101**.
syntax.say: When you don't have permission to manage messages, the bot will include your name. Conversely, it will not.
